<h3 id="binding-transmitter-to-the-receiver">Binding transmitter to the receiver</h3>
<ol>
  <li>
    <p>You can bind your transmitter with at least the following things. Note taht the binding process differs from teh RC receiverâ€™s model to model. (binding cable, esc, servo motor, battery)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Connect the binding cable to rc receiver on the BAT pinor B/VCC</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Tane an ESC to connect the signal, 5V and ground. (Remember, the outer pin of a row is for the ground, the middle pin is for 5V, and the inner pin is for the signal.)</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="aero-dynamics">Aero-dynamics</h3>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Â </th>
      <th>Â </th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>TAu, vector product of force (F), distance (r)</td>
      <td><img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42961200/126632875-860a1985-a54e-4cb3-b5c4-cb86ac7a0ccd.png" alt="image" /></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>0 is the angle between force and distance from the center of axis</td>
      <td><img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42961200/126632924-71eb802d-494c-4de6-8011-6112b66b00b1.png" alt="image" /></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<ul>
  <li>thrust is the product of pressure (P) and area (A), Thrust = P x A</li>
</ul>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Â </th>
      <th>Â </th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td><img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42961200/126633487-c13da5f6-a842-440e-b5fa-5eebfe8a360d.png" alt="image" /></td>
      <td><img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42961200/126633341-757efd61-f18c-4177-99c7-6fe787234a0b.png" alt="image" /></td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>Thrust (T) will be proportional to the square of the angular velocity (w) of the propellers. The thrust is perpendicular to the Z direction of the drone.</p>

<p><img src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/42961200/126633753-52ef95b0-4d27-4c53-8c6c-cf4812064854.png" alt="image" /></p>

